{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":425811,"duration_api_ms":446831,"num_turns":29,"result":"The implementation is complete. Here's what I built:\n\n## Implementation Complete\n\n### What was built (single file: `docs/index.html`)\n\n**Content/Features:**\n- **Opportunity Regions Panel:** 5 ranked unexplored composition regions with coordinates, density scores, priority ranking (high/medium), nearby material context (max Tc, avg mass), and click-to-focus in 3D viz with green sphere markers + vertical guide lines\n- **High-Tc Materials List:** Top 20 materials sorted by Tc (toggleable to 10/50) showing atomic mass, radius, valence, cluster assignment, and Tc value. Click to zoom in 3D.\n- **Cluster Analysis:** 3 clusters displayed with count, percentage, avg/max Tc, avg mass, avg valence, and proportional bar charts\n- **About Overlay:** Full strategic context covering GNoME complementarity, autonomous lab prioritization, hypothesis generation, and integration roadmap\n- **Interactive Features:** Hover tooltips on points (Tc, cluster, mass, radius, valence, PCA coords), click to zoom, panel collapse/expand, material count toggles, color mode switching (Tc vs Cluster), region visibility toggle, keyboard shortcuts (R=rotate, Esc=close)\n\n**Visual/Branding:**\n- Cream background (#F5F3ED)\n- Fragment Mono font throughout\n- Dark text on light backgrounds\n- Minimal, professional design with subtle borders and backdrop blur\n\n**Technical:**\n- All panels in right sidebar (320px) with scroll, no overlapping\n- Stats bar at bottom-left\n- CDN Three.js + OrbitControls (reliable loading)\n- Raycaster-based hover/click interaction\n- Sub-second render with 5K point sample\n\n### Ready to deploy\n\nWould you like me to commit and push to deploy to GitHub Pages?\n\n```\n✓ Opportunity regions panel: 5 regions displayed with priorities\n✓ Top materials list: 20 materials sorted by Tc (toggle 10/20/50)\n✓ Cluster analysis: 3 clusters with full stats\n✓ Strategic context overlay: complete\n✓ Cream background + Fragment Mono\n✓ All features functional, no overlaps\n✓ JS syntax validated, HTML structure verified\n✓ Tested locally: serves correctly at localhost:8888\n```","stop_reason":null,"session_id":"ea4c7d20-555a-44c2-8feb-537f7e876054","total_cost_usd":1.5552395499999994,"usage":{"input_tokens":27,"cache_creation_input_tokens":31558,"cache_read_input_tokens":957840,"output_tokens":18968,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":31558,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":29783,"outputTokens":8968,"cacheReadInputTokens":303428,"cacheCreationInputTokens":33928,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.14737580000000006,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":37,"outputTokens":25313,"cacheReadInputTokens":1011645,"cacheCreationInputTokens":43045,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.4078637499999995,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01L9vApnfc5PLUafaHfFe1v2","tool_input":{"command":"du -h /Users/03-mac-alpha/.openclaw/workspace/supersearch/docs/lib/*","description":"Check size of library files"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01X4rVJcdwUsuqgvnyR7isdC","tool_input":{"command":"wc -l /Users/03-mac-alpha/.openclaw/workspace/supersearch/docs/index*.html","description":"Compare HTML file sizes"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_017yAxrEewPHeYPTmsuFAcam","tool_input":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('docs/data/analysis_results_fast.json') as f:\n    data = json.load(f)\n\n# Top structure\nprint('Keys:', list(data.keys()))\nprint('Materials count:', len(data['materials']))\nprint('Sparse regions count:', len(data.get('sparse_regions', [])))\nprint()\n\n# Metadata\nprint('Metadata:', json.dumps(data.get('metadata', {}), indent=2))\nprint()\n\n# Sample materials\nprint('First material:', json.dumps(data['materials'][0], indent=2))\nprint()\n\n# Sparse regions\nprint('Sparse regions:')\nfor r in data.get('sparse_regions', []):\n    print(json.dumps(r))\nprint()\n\n# Top 5 by Tc\ntop = sorted(data['materials'], key=lambda m: m['tc'], reverse=True)[:10]\nprint('Top 10 by Tc:')\nfor m in top:\n    print(f'  tc={m[\\\"tc\\\"]}K cluster={m[\\\"cluster\\\"]} mass={m[\\\"atomic_mass\\\"]:.1f} radius={m[\\\"atomic_radius\\\"]:.1f} valence={m[\\\"valence\\\"]:.2f} x={m[\\\"x\\\"]:.2f} y={m[\\\"y\\\"]:.2f}')\n\n# Cluster distribution\nfrom collections import Counter\nclusters = Counter(m['cluster'] for m in data['materials'])\nprint()\nprint('Cluster distribution:', dict(clusters))\n\n# Tc stats per cluster\nfor c in sorted(clusters.keys()):\n    cluster_mats = [m for m in data['materials'] if m['cluster'] == c]\n    tcs = [m['tc'] for m in cluster_mats]\n    print(f'  Cluster {c}: n={len(cluster_mats)}, avg_tc={sum(tcs)/len(tcs):.1f}K, max_tc={max(tcs):.1f}K, min_tc={min(tcs):.4f}K')\n\"\n","description":"Analyze JSON data structure and statistics"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01PZXLEpnbe7SZCsw3v9FTon","tool_input":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('docs/data/analysis_results_fast.json') as f:\n    data = json.load(f)\n\nprint('Keys:', list(data.keys()))\nprint('Materials count:', len(data['materials']))\nprint('Sparse regions count:', len(data.get('sparse_regions', [])))\nprint()\nprint('Metadata:', json.dumps(data.get('metadata', {}), indent=2))\nprint()\nprint('First material:', json.dumps(data['materials'][0], indent=2))\nprint()\nprint('Sparse regions:')\nfor r in data.get('sparse_regions', []):\n    print(json.dumps(r))\nprint()\n\ntop = sorted(data['materials'], key=lambda m: m['tc'], reverse=True)[:10]\nprint('Top 10 by Tc:')\nfor m in top:\n    print(f'  tc={m[\\\"tc\\\"]}K cluster={m[\\\"cluster\\\"]} mass={m[\\\"atomic_mass\\\"]:.1f} radius={m[\\\"atomic_radius\\\"]:.1f} valence={m[\\\"valence\\\"]:.2f} x={m[\\\"x\\\"]:.2f} y={m[\\\"y\\\"]:.2f}')\n\nfrom collections import Counter\nclusters = Counter(m['cluster'] for m in data['materials'])\nprint()\nprint('Cluster distribution:', dict(clusters))\nfor c in sorted(clusters.keys()):\n    cluster_mats = [m for m in data['materials'] if m['cluster'] == c]\n    tcs = [m['tc'] for m in cluster_mats]\n    print(f'  Cluster {c}: n={len(cluster_mats)}, avg_tc={sum(tcs)/len(tcs):.1f}K, max_tc={max(tcs):.1f}K, min_tc={min(tcs):.4f}K')\n\"\n","description":"Analyze JSON data structure and statistics"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_016b5VKg5tJGS8aDeSsUqCYv","tool_input":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('docs/data/analysis_results_fast.json') as f:\n    data = json.load(f)\nprint('Keys:', list(data.keys()))\nprint('Materials count:', len(data['materials']))\nprint('Sparse regions:', len(data.get('sparse_regions',[])))\nprint('Metadata:', json.dumps(data.get('metadata',{}), indent=2))\nprint('First material:', json.dumps(data['materials'][0], indent=2))\nprint('Sparse regions data:')\nfor r in data.get('sparse_regions',[]):\n    print(' ', json.dumps(r))\ntop = sorted(data['materials'], key=lambda m: m['tc'], reverse=True)[:10]\nprint('Top 10 by Tc:')\nfor m in top:\n    print(f'  tc={m[\\\"tc\\\"]}K cluster={m[\\\"cluster\\\"]} mass={m[\\\"atomic_mass\\\"]:.1f} radius={m[\\\"atomic_radius\\\"]:.1f} valence={m[\\\"valence\\\"]:.2f}')\nfrom collections import Counter\nclusters = Counter(m['cluster'] for m in data['materials'])\nprint('Cluster dist:', dict(clusters))\nfor c in sorted(clusters.keys()):\n    cm = [m for m in data['materials'] if m['cluster'] == c]\n    tcs = [m['tc'] for m in cm]\n    print(f'  Cluster {c}: n={len(cm)} avg_tc={sum(tcs)/len(tcs):.1f}K max_tc={max(tcs):.1f}K')\n\"\n","description":"Analyze JSON data structure and statistics"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01RyNSnZ2tR